<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>It would be really great if there would be the possibility to get the results of fetchAll() not only as a continous array but indexed by one of the columns of the result.
That means having a table with two columns
country_id and country_name 
for example it would be great to make a call like fetchAll(..., 'country_id') and get an array like</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1 =&gt; 'country_1',
2 =&gt; 'country_2',
...
</code></pre>

<p>or even</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
1 =&gt; array(
                    country_id =&gt; 1,
                    country_name =&gt; 'country_1',
                  ),
2 =&gt; array(
                    country_id =&gt; 2,
                    country_name =&gt; 'country_2',
                  ),
</code></pre>

